Chlorine Purification

The facility fills chlorine ton containers to various purity grades. Commercial grade liquid chlorine is received in ton containers. Once the containers arrive at the facility they are offloaded and placed in the designated storage area until needed for purification. When the receiving tons are filled with the required purity grade, they are carted back to the storage area.   When chlorine ton containers are ordered, they are transferred to Building 200 for pickup.

Cylinder Storage

The facility is regulated for the storage of the chemical cylinders listed above.  Some cylinders are filled onsite and then carted to the storage area.  Other cylinders are delivered by either a vendor or other Matheson Tri-Gas, Inc. sites.  The cylinders are stored onsite until distribution to customers.

ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION PROGRAM AND CHEMICAL-SPECIFIC PREVENTION STEPS

Matheson Tri-Gas, Inc. has developed an accidental release prevention program for compliance with OSHA's PSM and EPA's RMP regulations.  The program includes but is not limited to the following elements:

¿	Safety information regarding the chemical hazards, and operating and technical specifications for the equipment;
¿	Written procedures for operating and maintaining the processes;
¿	Training for employees involved with process operations and maintenance;
¿	Written procedures for managing system changes and startup of a modified process;
¿	Investigating releases and near misses and implementing measures to prevent recurrence;
¿	Written procedures for conducting hot work on or near the covered processes;
¿	Contractor management policies to ensure contract employee safety while on facility premises; and
¿	Employee involvement in program development and implementation.  

